





	
                
                Parameter Tree:

                
                    EARTH SCIENCE > ATMOSPHERE > ATMOSPHERIC TEMPERATURE > INVERSION HEIGHT

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    The height of the layer in which air temperature increases with
altitude, representing an "inversion" of the typical temperature decrease
with height in the troposphere. 
                
                

                

                
                    Reference:

                    
                        
                            Glossary of Weather and Climate, American Meteorological Society, 1996. 
                        
                    
                    

                    

                
            


       







    
    
    
        
    

    
